Override `CreateWindow` in your `App` class and attach handlers to all six events:

```csharp
public partial class App : Application
{
    protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
    {
        var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);

        window.Created     += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine("[Lifecycle] Created");
        window.Activated   += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine("[Lifecycle] Activated");
        window.Deactivated += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine("[Lifecycle] Deactivated");
        window.Stopped     += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine("[Lifecycle] Stopped");
        window.Resumed     += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine("[Lifecycle] Resumed");
        window.Destroying  += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine("[Lifecycle] Destroying");

        return window;
    }
}
```

**Key things to know:**

- **First launch** fires `Created → Activated` (not `Resumed`).
- **Backgrounding** fires `Deactivated → Stopped`.
- **Returning** fires `Resumed → Activated`.
- **`Resumed` never fires on first launch** — only after a `Stopped`.
- On **Android**, the back button can skip `Stopped` and go straight to `Destroying`, so log both if you're tracking exits.

If you also need the raw **platform-native** callbacks, add `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(a => a
        .OnCreate((act, b) => Debug.WriteLine("Android OnCreate"))
        .OnResume(act    => Debug.WriteLine("Android OnResume"))
        .OnPause(act     => Debug.WriteLine("Android OnPause"))
        .OnStop(act      => Debug.WriteLine("Android OnStop"))
        .OnDestroy(act   => Debug.WriteLine("Android OnDestroy")));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidBecomeActive(app      => Debug.WriteLine("iOS DidBecomeActive"))
        .WillResignActive(app     => Debug.WriteLine("iOS WillResignActive"))
        .DidEnterBackground(app   => Debug.WriteLine("iOS DidEnterBackground"))
        .WillEnterForeground(app  => Debug.WriteLine("iOS WillEnterForeground")));
#endif
});
```

This gives you a complete debug trace of every state transition on all platforms.
